# Spotify Listening Habits Analysis

## Project Overview
This project analyzes personal Spotify playlist data to explore listening habits, 
artist preferences, and song popularity. The goal is to gain insight into how playlists 
are structured and how music choices vary across playlists.

## Tools Used
- Python
- Jupyter Notebook
- Spotify Web API
- pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn

## Questions Explored
- How many songs are in each playlist?
- Which artists appear most frequently across playlists?
- What does the distribution of song popularity look like?
- How do playlists differ in size and composition?

## Files in This Repository
- `Untitled1.ipynb` – Jupyter Notebook containing data collection, cleaning, analysis, and visualizations
- `cleaned_tracks_df.csv` – Cleaned dataset extracted from the Spotify Web API
- `Project_Summary.pdf` – One-page written summary of the project
- `Final_Presentation.pptx` – Final presentation slides
- `README.md` – Project overview and file descriptions

## Dataset Source
Spotify Web API  
https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api
